5. List of Technologies/API's Used
  - Goodreads API
  - SQLAlchemy
  - WTForms
  - Bootstrap templates
  - User Session Management
  - Flask
6. Detailed Description of the project (No more than 500 words)
This application is called Book-Keeper. A user can add books that they have read
and see a list of all the books they read in the past.

7. List of Controllers and their short description (No more than 50 words for each controller)
- login: redirection to login.html page
- logout: redirection to login.html page after clicking logging out
- register: redirection to registration.html for registering an account
- about: page for the application's description
- dashboard: redirection to a user's dashboard displays their book database
            and allows them to add new books to the database

8. List of Views and their short description (No more than 50 words for each view)
- layout.html: the template that is extended by other views
- login.html: page for logging in
- register.html: page for registering a new account
- dashboard.html: page for displaying a user's books database
- about.html: page for description of the application
- home.html: welcome page for the application
- _navbar.html: nav bar that is used for all pages

9. List of Tables, their Structure and short description
- Books table:
    structure: id, title, year, rating, image_url, ownder_id
    Lists all books that are added by users. All book titles are unique. It keeps
    track of book title, year published, rating and image url.
- Authors table:
    structure: author, author name, books they have written that are in the book list
    
- Readers table: an association table to keep track of unique lists of books for each user.
The table keeps track of which book a specific user has in his/her list.
e.g user1 will have a different book list to user2

10. References/Resources: List all the references, resources or the online templates that were used for the project.
https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css
